      "text": "COVID-19 spreads mainly through inhaling air contaminated by droplets and aerosols from infected individuals.",
      "citations": ["doc1_covid19.txt:chunk_00004"]
    },
    {
      "text": "Infected individuals exhale virus-containing particles when they breathe, talk, cough, sneeze, or sing.",
      "citations": ["doc1_covid19.txt:chunk_00004"]
    },
    {
      "text": "Transmission is most likely at close range but can occur over longer distances, especially indoors.",
      "citations": ["doc1_covid19.txt:chunk_00004"]
    },
    {
      "text": "COVID-19 can also spread when infectious particles come into contact with the eyes, nose, or mouth.",
      "citations": ["doc1_covid19.txt:chunk_00004"]
    },
    {
      "text": "Touching surfaces contaminated with the virus and then touching the face can also lead to transmission.",
      "citations": ["doc1_covid19.txt:chunk_00004"]
    },
    {
      "text": "People can remain contagious for up to 20 days and may spread the virus without showing symptoms.",
      "citations": ["doc1_covid19.txt:chunk_00004"]
    }
  ]
}

